==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[þistel]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪsəl|-ɪsəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of several [[perennial]] [[composite]] [[plant]]s, of [[genera]] ''[[Cirsium]], [[Carduus]] or [[Onopordum]]'', having [[prickly]] [[leaves]] and [[showy]] [[flower head]]s with prickly [[bract]]s.
# The [[national]] [[emblem]] of [[Scotland]].

====Quotations====
*{{RQ:Authorized Version}}, Genesis 3:18
*: Thorns also and '''thistles''' shall it bring forth to thee; and thou shalt eat the herb of the field;

